@NODE What "What is SuperFresh"

o What is SuperFresh
  -------------------

Superfresh is a replacement for the DLG's Freshen command, and its based
on Luca Spada's "Skyfreshen".

The Freshen command is used to rebuild the File.Dat (a file index present in
all your file areas) reading all the area's xxx.fd.

SuperFresh features :

- Its faster than DLG's Freshen
- Areas to be refreshed can be specified on command line
- Can freshen without setting comments on files (faster)
- Can optionally delete non-existing entries from file areas
- Handles extended filepaths
- cause DLG v1.2.3 have a bug so if you use closeareas the password "DLG"
  is used by default, so you must use this password to reopen the area again.
  SuperFresh knows the bug and works using the righ password for closing or
  opening a area.

SuperFresh is FREE-WARE, but if you like it, feel free to send me a postcard
from your city. It's nice to know that someone uses my utility.


@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage "Usage"

o Usage
  =====

SuperFresh V1.0 - by I.Chatziandreou, Bochum, FRG
Fido: 2:2443/1151.0, UUCP: greeky@ouzonix.ruhr.de
based on Luca Spadas SkyFreshen
 
Usage:
SuperFresh [DELETE] [NOCOM] [<ALL>] [<Low Area>-<Hi Area>] [<Area> <...>]
           [-<Area to skip> <...>]

 DELETE   - Delete non existing file entries
 NOCOM    - Does not set the ("FILE:xx/yy.fd") comment on files

Examples:

1> SuperFresh DELETE 200-300 34-70 -50 -51

Will freshen areas from 200 to 300 and from 34 to 70 except 50 and 51 and
will delete non existing file entries

1> SuperFresh NOCOM ALL -10

Will freshen all areas except area 10 and will not set the comment on 
processed files (this speed up SuperFresh of 20-30%).
      
                         
    
